Job Title: Senior Business Analyst - General Insurance Transformation - Discovery
Ad Text:
Senior Business Analyst - General Insurance Transformation - Discovery

This is a new 12-month contract role based in Sydney, focusing on a large-scale General Insurance transformation project. The role begins in a Discovery capacity of a new insurance platform, with an expectation to transition into the delivery phase.

Essential Experience:

To be successful in the role, candidates must meet these non-negotiable criteria:

General Insurance Background: 100% mandatory. Good understanding of the insurance ecosystem.
Core Insurance Domains: Experience working with underwriters and claims stakeholders by yourself and are comfortable interviewing them alone.
Discovery Phase Experience: Proven ability to work in the early stages of a project, uncovering requirements, defining "as-is" flows, and performing gap analysis.
End-to-End Lifecycle: Ability to start in Discovery and transition into Delivery
Large-Scale Transformation: Experience on complex, multi-release projects or cloud platform migrations.
Technical & Soft Skills

Platform Knowledge: Guidewire experience is highly preferred but not mandatory. However, experience with similar cloud-based insurance platforms is a significant advantage.
Stakeholder Management: Ability to independently lead sessions with a broad cohort, including underwriters, agents, and claims officers.
Discovery Tooling: Experience populating Discovery Documents and transitioning them into "Inception" (moving from high-level to granular detail).
Attributes: Self-starter, curious, determined, and comfortable working in ambiguity.
Mapping transactional flows and conducting gap analysis against to identify what needs to be reused, extended, or created from scratch.
Moving from high-level requirements to the next level of technical detail.

Our client, a Federal Government department based in Barton, ACT, that is responsible for foreign policy and international relations, requires the services of a senior Business Analyst for a 12 + 12-month contract.

Duties of the Business Analyst:

Analyse complex system requirements and communicate these to both technical counterparts and non-technical business users.
Gather, refine and document user requirements using various techniques which include but are not limited to interviews, document analysis, requirements workshops, surveys, business process descriptions, use cases, scenarios, business analysis, task and workflow analysis.
Prepare reports, business cases and risk management analysis to support ICT system projects.
Liaise with, provide advice, and respond appropriately to stakeholders on matters that relate to project requirements.
Develop and maintain collaborative and productive relationships with internal and external stakeholders.
Assist with implementation of projects by undertaking system design and specification, including analysis of business processes.
Ongoing system administration and configuration as required.
Contribute to development of training, standard operating procedures and helpcard resources on systems.
Instigate and enable organisational change in the Division and Department for new business processes.
Deliver ongoing improvements to business processes and system functionality.
Develop other deliverables as required for emerging needs.¬†

Skills and Experience - Business Analyst:

Demonstrated experience as a business analyst working on significant ICT projects, ideally within Australian government environments.
Ability to define clear, measurable acceptance criteria to ensure features and functions meet business requirements and are fit for purpose.
Strong communication skills and the ability to engage with stakeholders at all levels.
High level of initiative and the ability to work independently.
Ability to maintain a high degree of discretion when dealing with sensitive information.

Job Title: Senior Corporate Analyst | Big 4 Second Mover
Ad Text:
High profile Infrastructure giant is amid large-scale transformation. This is a highly complex business and its operations span across Australia.¬†

The Transformation Director is seeking a high-performing Senior Corporate Analyst to support the execution of a complex, multi-year transition. This role will play a key part in supporting the development of a strategic partnership, with a focus on, capital program, project execution, transition planning, and stakeholder alignment.

This is a 6-month contract to permanent opportunity.¬†

Key duties include:

Support execution of a complex, multi-year strategic partnership, contributing to operational readiness, diligence, and transition planning activities.
Operate within a PMO environment, tracking progress, managing dependencies, and supporting issue/risk escalation and resolution.
Prepare executive-ready materials, dashboards, and analysis to support senior stakeholder communication and governance forums.
Coordinate cross-functional workstreams and external advisors to ensure timely alignment of milestones, deliverables, and decision points.
Support procurement and capital planning analysis on ad hoc basis
Exposure and opportunity to add input to commercial terms considering transitional service considerations, and value preservation opportunities
Key criteria to be considered:

CA/CPA/CFA qualified ideally¬†
Big 4 Second mover with exposure to¬†transformations, M&A, or FP&A within complex environment.¬†
Sector experience in infrastructure, industrials or other capital-intensive industries
Exceptional communication and stakeholder management

Our black belt specialists are leaders in their domains: digital champions, delivery-focused experts, top-tier security professionals, AI thought leaders, and engineering best practice advocates.

With a global presence and local expertise, we deliver innovative solutions without compromising on quality. Our multidisciplinary teams provide tailored expertise to solve complex problems at scale, ensuring engineering excellence through our top technologists.

Empower Your Career with Us

Are you ready to join a dynamic team that empowers businesses through robust engineering capabilities? We seek talented individuals who thrive in a fast-paced environment with a strong sense of urgency and a focus on execution.

Overview of the Role

We are seeking an experienced Senior Power BI Developer to design, build, and optimise enterprise-grade analytics and reporting solutions for complex client environments. You will work closely with data engineers, product teams, and senior stakeholders to translate business questions into clear, high-impact insights.

This role is hands-on and delivery-focused, suited to someone who enjoys owning analytics outcomes end-to-end, from data modelling through to executive-ready dashboards.

Australian work rights are required for this position.

Key Responsibilities

Design and develop scalable Power BI dashboards and reports for enterprise and regulated environments
Model complex datasets using star schemas and best-practice semantic layer design
Build and optimise DAX measures with a strong focus on performance and maintainability
Partner with data engineers to shape data pipelines and ensure reporting-ready data models
Work directly with stakeholders to define KPIs, reporting requirements, and analytical outcomes
Implement row-level security and governance controls aligned to data security standards
Drive consistency, quality, and usability across reporting solutions
Contribute to analytics standards, patterns, and best practices across engagements

Skills and Experience

Required:

Strong commercial experience delivering Power BI solutions in production environments
Advanced Power BI development skills including DAX, Power Query (M), and data modelling
Experience working with SQL-based data platforms (e.g. SQL Server, Azure SQL, Snowflake, Synapse)
Proven ability to translate complex business requirements into clear, actionable insights
Experience working in agile, delivery-focused teams
Strong communication skills and confidence engaging with senior stakeholders

Preferred:

Experience in financial services, insurance, or other regulated industries
Exposure to Azure data services (ADF, Synapse, Fabric)
Experience designing analytics for large-scale or multi-tenant platforms
Understanding of data governance, security, and access control patterns
Experience working alongside AI, ML, or advanced analytics teams

This is a unique opportunity to shape the future of our analytics and data capability through high-impact Power BI solutions. The successful candidate will be both a strategic thinker and a hands-on practitioner, capable of delivering trusted insights that drive financial, operational, and decision-making outcomes at scale.
